This paper is about using Natural Language Processing techniques to investigate a specific phishing campaign, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing the semantic similarity between the senders' CV attachments and the recipients' LinkedIn profiles, which involves natural language processing techniques such as Latent Semantic Analysis (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses statistical analysis to draw conclusions about the targeted nature of the phishing campaign, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also involves analyzing text data to draw conclusions, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper is about characterizing phishing threats, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
